The paper deals with parameterized complexity and combinatorial optimization problems involving linear equations, which are topics commonly studied in computer science theory. Specifically, the paper focuses on the \textsc{MaxLin2-AA}[$k$] and \textsc{Max-$r$-Lin2-AA}[$k,r$] problems, which are related to constraint satisfaction and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves combinatorial optimization and graph theory, which are covered by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper uses techniques from information theory, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory).
